[4] Saudi Arabia, 1 new fatal case - MOH 12 Jun 2015, RFI
Date: Fri 12 Jun 2015
Source: Saudi Arabia Ministry of Health [edited]
http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/statistics-2015-06-12-001.aspx


As of 12 noon today (12 Jun 2015), there have been a total of:
1030 laboratory-confirmed cases of MERS-CoV infection, including
453 deaths
568 recoveries, and
9 cases currently active including 1 case on home isolation

In the past 24 hours, there has been
1 newly confirmed fatal case reported

Information on newly confirmed fatal case:
A 77-year-old Saudi male, non-healthcare worker from Hufoof was report as newly confirmed case. At the time of the initial report on 12 Jun 2015 the patient had reportedly expired. He was noted to have had a history of pre-existing co-morbidities, and to have had contact with another case(s) in either the healthcare environment or the community.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The outbreak in Hufoof continues on a slow but steady pace, with 31 cases including 15 deaths reported since 20 Apr 2015. Again the overwhelming majority of cases have a history of contact with other cases. This outbreak has continued now for over 3 incubation periods. A question that comes to mind is: What are the specific transmission chains? How many generations of cases have been documented? And is the transmission purely nosocomial now or is there a community transmission component as well?

Do any of our readers in Saudi Arabia have any answers to these questions? ProMED-mail would greatly appreciate more information.

A map showing the location of Hufoof can be found at the source URL. - Mod.MPP]
